esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when pods are not ready and in a failed or pending state.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Pod status ready=false with phase failed or pending, excluding evicted pods.
//
// What it means:
// Pods unable to serve traffic — potential service degradation.
//
// Common causes:
// Image pull errors, resource constraints, crash loops, configuration issues.
//
// Grouped by cluster, pod name, and namespace for investigation.
TS metrics-kubernetes.pod-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.pod.status.ready` == "false"
  AND (`kubernetes.pod.status.phase` == "failed" OR `kubernetes.pod.status.phase` == "pending")
  AND (`kubernetes.pod.status.reason` IS NULL OR `kubernetes.pod.status.reason` != "evicted")
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.pod.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
